<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,403,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath, 1981" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="1981" box="[665,1047,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linnavuorii">
<emphasis box="[665,688,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[703,827,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">linnavuorii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath" box="[835,1047,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. (1981) Indian Macropsinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). II. Species described by W. L. Distant and descriptions of new species from the Indian subconunent. Entomologica Scandinavica, 12, 295 - 310." type="journal article" year="1981">
Viraktamath, 
<number box="[988,1047,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter one by relatively small and nearly apical gonopore, more slender and longer pygofer processes bent outwards and by different shape of styles.
</paragraph>
